# Omninuera — AI Intern Offer Letter

Date: [Start Date]

To: [Candidate Full Name]

Subject: Offer of Internship — AI Intern

Dear [Candidate Full Name],

We are pleased to offer you an internship position with Omninuera for the role of **AI Intern** on the terms set out in this letter.

1. Role and Duration
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months, commencing on [Start Date] and ending approximately three months thereafter unless earlier terminated in accordance with this letter.

2. Employment Type and Location
- Employment type: Internship / temporary engagement. This is an internship and does not confer any employee status or entitlement to employee benefits unless explicitly stated in writing by Omninuera.
- Work location: Fully remote. The candidate is based in Bengaluru and is expected to work remotely.

3. Stipend
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month. This amount is explicitly a stipend (not salary) and is intended to support the internship engagement.
- Stipend payment schedule: Paid monthly via bank transfer to the account details provided by you. Please provide your banking information in the placeholder below:
  - Bank details for stipend payment: [Bank Account Details for Stipend].

4. Expected Weekly Commitment
- Expected weekly commitment: Approximately 20–40 hours per week (suggested range). This is a flexible, remote arrangement and exact weekly hours can be agreed with your reporting manager to accommodate project needs and your availability.

5. Reporting and Supervision
- Reporting manager: [Reporting Manager]. You will report to and coordinate with [Reporting Manager] (or their delegate) for day-to-day assignments, progress reviews, and feedback.

6. Key Responsibilities
You will be expected to engage in tasks including, but not limited to:
- Data preparation and cleaning for model training and evaluation.
- Designing and running model experiments and prototypes.
- Model evaluation, performance analysis, and metric reporting.
- Documentation of experiments, code, and findings.
- Collaboration with the Omninuera team, including attending scheduled remote meetings and contributing to project discussions.

7. Confidentiality and Intellectual Property
- Confidentiality: During the internship and thereafter, you must maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera’s confidential information, trade secrets, client data, models, code, documentation, business plans, and other proprietary information. You shall not disclose, use, or permit the use of such confidential information except as required to perform your duties for Omninuera and as permitted in writing.
- IP assignment: You agree that all inventions, discoveries, developments, works of authorship, designs, source code, algorithms, improvements, and other intellectual property (collectively, "IP") conceived, developed, or reduced to practice by you, alone or with others, during the course of the internship and related to Omninuera’s business or using Omninuera’s resources, shall be the exclusive property of Omninuera. You hereby assign (and agree to assign) to Omninuera all right, title, and interest in such IP. You agree to execute any documents reasonably requested by Omninuera to effectuate such assignment.
- These confidentiality obligations and IP assignment will survive the termination of the internship.

8. Termination / Early Exit
- Either party may terminate this internship by providing one (1) week written notice to the other party.
- Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for cause (including, but not limited to, breach of confidentiality, gross misconduct, serious policy violations, or other material breaches of this agreement).

9. Conditions
- This offer and your participation in the internship are subject to:
  - Legal compliance review by Omninuera’s legal department.
  - Background verification and any other pre-engagement checks as may be applicable and communicated to you.
- If the legal department requests changes to the terms, HR will coordinate implementation of those changes and provide you with an updated offer.

10. Governing Law and Jurisdiction
- This agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws applicable in Bengaluru, India. Any disputes arising under or relating to this offer will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts in Bengaluru, India.

11. Miscellaneous
- Entire agreement: This letter contains the full agreement between you and Omninuera with respect to the internship and supersedes all prior agreements or understandings (oral or written) related to the internship.
- Amendments: Any amendments to this letter must be in writing and signed by an authorized representative of Omninuera.
- No guarantee of future employment: This internship does not guarantee or imply any offer of permanent employment at the end of the internship.

12. Acceptance
To accept this offer, please sign and date below and return a scanned copy to HR.

